utStream)`\n  - `writeObject(ObjectOutputStream)`\n\nThe existing `JDKDSAPublicKeyTest` already uses the normal Java serialization API to exercise those hooks and validates the restored DSA public key state. The native run currently fails before entering `JDKDSAPublicKey.readObject` because Native Image lacks serialization/reflection metadata for allocation during deserialization (`java.lang.Object.<init>` metadata error). Per project rules, I did **not** add or edit Native Image/reachability metadata directly.\n\nI did not make another code change because any additional way to instantiate `JDKDSAPublicKey` would require package-private access, direct reflection, Unsafe allocation, or shadowing library classes, all of which violate the task constraints.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_084f39ee3f2fdcdf016a26092a72d881968383b218784ddaf4\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2944, "output": 775, "cacheRead": 69120, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 72839, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780877594420, "responseId": "resp_084f39ee3f2fdcdf016a26091b15f081969d80de655052a1f5"}}
